apitel herausgearbeitet und das agonale Verhältnis zwischen Erzähler und implizitem Leser beleuchtet.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aAulus Gellius. 4aMiszellanliteratur. 4aNoctes Atticae. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAulus Gellius.  aNoctes Atticae.  aliterary miscellany.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2020z9783110704631oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831106951440 cprintz978311069500740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110695083zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110695083zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110695083/original  a978-3-11-069627-1 DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-GOA